08/09/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu approved the launch of a criminal investigation against Defence Minister Teodor Atanasiu on Thursday (7 September). Local media reports suggest Basescu acted on the basis of recommendations from a special presidential commission, investigating allegations that Atanasiu might have endangered the lives of Romanian soldiers abroad by revealing classified information about their location. The minister has made no comment. (Ziua, Mediafax - 08/09/06)
